==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: thujone
<hw>thu"jone</hw> <pr>(th⟦umac⟧"j⟦omac⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<def>An oil, <chform>C10H16O</chform>, the chief constituent of cedar
leaf oil (thuja oil), which is obtained from the northern white cedar
(arbor vitae, <spn>Thuja occidentalis</spn>) or the western Red Cedar
(<spn>Thuja plicatis</spn>). It is a stimulant similar to camphor. It is
also called <altname>thujol</altname>, <altname>thuyol</altname>,
<altname>absinthol</altname>, <altname>thuyone</altname>,
<altname>tanacetol</altname>, and <altname>tanacetone</altname>.</def>
<au>Stedman.</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thule</ent>⟦br⟧
